rComments: Tough class but prof was a gem

Prof Leblanc is a great prof! He is available outside of class to answer questions and give hints to homework questions, and he posts the lectures (in form of YT videos) several days before the class so that you can digest the material before class. Analysis is extremely difficult, but Prof Leblanc does his best to make it bearable.

Good choice for MAT2522 and MAT2525 - lots of time to ask questions and he really wants to make sure you understand. Two hard classes (especially real analysis), but assignments and exams are fair if you put in the work and study.

I think that he just changed his way of grading (compare to previous ratings). He no longer have midterms, only quizzes, assignments and final. He said that the final will be like the quizzes (easy) and only multiple choice. So you don't have to worry about tough grader. He is very well organized. Do his exercices and you will easily get an A.

For an online class, it's very good. There will be a quizz every week (that's good to keep you update), no midterms and 6 assignments. It seems a lot but it's for your own good. His lectures are already recorded and very clear. If you want to pass, do his additional exercices (they are so helpful if you don't understand). He's a very good prof !
He's a great lecturer. Only reason I wouldn't take him again is because he makes the final overly difficult. Also wish he had provided practice finals/midterms
Good prof. He curved everybody generously. His office hour is very helpful, he can explain everything clearly. Will take him again.
Amazing lecturer but tough final. Midterm had a fair difficulty level

Don't take calc 3 with him. He makes the midterms and especially his final super difficult. Avoid at all costs. He is also extremely rude so don't bother attending his office hours. He is also a tough grader. Deducts marks like crazy for small mistakes.

good teacher but he was rude to our class and snaked us on the second midterm and final, i got a on the first midterm it was pretty easy, i did worse than i should have on final and second midterm but he shouldnt have made them as hard as he did, just because the class did good on the first one, not a good attitude

He is an AMAZING professor and he was an amazing prof before. He is the best professor in the whole university. If you want to do well, you need to attend all of the lectures, since his lectures are perfect.

He is good at teaching and his classes are not bad but super rude in person. I had a class with him last year and he wasn't this rude. I feel like since he became the vice dean he has been super stressed and is taking it out on the students. Greets you with "if you are here for marks leave." when you enter his office. Study and you will get an A.

He is not bad but was extremely rude in office hours. Refused to look at my midterm even though there was a mistake on it. Midterm 1 was really easy, Midterm 2 was really difficult, final was in between midterm 1 and 2. His notes are alright. Would give higher rating if he wasn't so mean..
An amazing prof, kind of intimidating but teaches well and also posts his notes. gives suggested homework problems and posts several past exams to help you study. recommend him for any math course!

Fantastic prof, he's on the level of the greats like Desjardin and Khoury. Not particularly hard as long as you practice some stuff and don't fall behind. He posts his lecture notes that he wrote in class on the "smart board" online and gives you solutions to suggested problems in the textbook. Stimulating lectures, overall good guy.
Really good prof, just realized he looks like Todd McLellan :P you can get by with just past exams and midterms that he posts. Lectures are rlly helpful
AMAZING CALC PROF. dont do the problems in the textbook they just make you more confused. Explains concepts perfectly and exams are starightforward
his lectures are never boring and he explains perfectly!

Victor is the best prof to explain abstract mathematical concepts. He is engaging and his office hours are a lifesaver considering that this course is, to cite him, "the hardest class you'll have taken up to now". Do as many exercises as you can and you'll be fine.

One of the best lecturers in math.  Every time you enter a lecture he is very energetic.  His midterm and final are fair and they are no real surprises,  given that  you work hard and know what you are doing.  Highly recommended.

He really knows what he is talking about and he is very energetic. All his lectures notes are uploaded to blackboard so if you miss a class you are not screwed. You will need the book and don't study just by redoing previous midterms.

I had him for calc 3 and he is the most straight forward, clear cut prof i've ever met. He does not complicate things and there are actually no surprises doing midterms and finals. I never even did the recommended questions from the book. if you do the past exams he posts it will be an easy A for you.

He doesn't really explain the concept well during class lecture, tbh i understood him more during his office hour. His midterms are kinda difficult even with the old midterms practice, the textbook is very essential and helpful(i kinda understood with the examples and lots of practice problems he assigned).
Best I've had at OttawaU!  Amazing lectures, very clear, and funny.
Best I've had at OttawaU!
Easily one of the greatest professors at the university! Victor if you're reading this you're a legend and thank you for helping me!
Best prof I have ever had!
He is an amazing prof!

Incredible prof makes the material understandable for students. His tests are fair, just do the past midterms and you will be fine. Very clear and knows what he is doing and go to the lecture, you won't regret it.  Overall one of the best profs at uottawa.
Best teacher I've ever had

Consider yourself lucky if you have him for MAT2322. One of the best profs ever. Clear explanations and tells you exactly what you need to know.  Midterms and the final were very fair and similar to the sample exams he posted. No tricks at all. Simply the best.

Amazing prof to have for calc 3. He is funny, clear, and tells you exactly what he expects of you, tells you whats on the tests. The sample tests he gives reflect very strongly ( same type of problem, different numbers or shape) of the test you will get.  As the comment mentioned, I wish i could hug him. ( also a dude).
Wish I could hug him. And I'm a dude. Absolutely clear, easy, time relaxed midterms ever. Hope he doesn't disappoint in the final, though :p
Great Professor!

If you are an engineer student, consider youself extremely lucky to have the chance to take Cal 3 with him. With his immense knowledge and experience, he is indeed "THE BEST PROF" you can have for this class. Amazing lectures, examples explore applications of mathematics in engineering. He is also funny, which makes the class very interesting.
Awesome professor, explains the concept well and his teachings really helped me to understand further through my engineering courses. Highly recommend him

Despite it being a morning class, Complex Analysis was always worth going to because Victor presents the material at a reasonable pace and with great enthusiasm. Midterm was very representative of the material.

Probably the best math prof. I've had in all my undergrad.  Very clear explanations, speaks loud (sometimes a bit too loud :P) so the whole class can hear.  Keeps your attention.  Asks the class questions, but not difficult questions he doesn't expect anyone to answer.  Overall: excellent.  If Victor is teaching it, take it.

Excellent prof de math. Les notes, exercices supplémentaires, examens de pratiques, exercices de DGD sont tous sur le campus virtuel. Il est très organisé, les examens sont corrigés très rapidement. Il est très compréhensible et tu le vois qu'il aime ce qu'il enseigne.

Il est un très bon professeur de maths. Il explique très bien les concepts et en plus son cours est bien construit afin de voir les liens entre l'ensemble des choses apprissent tout au long de la session. Il peut parfois sembler bête quelque fois mais de façon général il est sympathique.

My 2nd best math professor I have had in university. He's really good and even provides online notes in case you miss a class (just don't miss a class if possible, his explanations are still required). Fair exams, though the 2nd midterm had a really low average for this course. Fortunately the final exam was really fair.
Excellent prof! Excellent human being. It very easy if you do the exercices in your book and on the internet. If you're from cegep you wont have to work hard !
Awesome prof who can actually teach, very willing to help... I agree with whoever said his voice goes supersonic. Celine cant even sing that high
An extremely helpful and nice teacher.  He really cares about his students.  If you are a student that works hard for your grade he will help you a lot.
I agree. He's definitely an angel. I've never see a prof that tries to help a student like he does.
this guy's simply an angel. he doesn't want to see u have bad marks.
tough but excellent teacher
Stern, Stern but fair (plus his Acadian accent rocks)

Very tough, but awesome prof. Voice like a cartoon character!
but no joke a good prof....

excellent calculus prof!  lectures are very clear
